This paper involves learning from demonstrations using a joint approach that integrates unsupervised structure learning with conventional imitation learning. The problem setting involves multiple coordinating agents, which suggests a focus on reinforcement learning and multi-agent systems. The application domain is team sports, which suggests a focus on computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
